{
  "Mirrors and Lenses": "镜镜和镜头",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is a concave mirror?": "什么是熔岩镜子?",
  "A concave (converging) mirror has an inward-curving reflecting surface. It focuses parallel light rays to a real focal point and can produce both real and virtual images depending on object placement.": "凝聚镜( 凝聚) 镜面有内向反射面。 它将平行的光线集中到一个真正的焦点, 并能够根据对象位置生成真实和虚拟图像 。",
  "What is a convex lens?": "什么是阴道透镜?",
  "A convex (converging) lens is thicker at the center and thinner at the edges. It refracts parallel light rays to converge at the focal point. It is used in magnifying glasses, cameras, and the human eye.": "相形( 相形) 镜片在中间更厚, 在边缘更薄。 它会折射平行的光线, 以便聚集在焦点点。 它用于放大镜、 相机和人的眼睛 。",
  "What is a real image?": "什么是真实形象?",
  "A real image is formed at a location where light rays actually converge (intersect). It can be captured on a screen and is typically inverted with respect to the object.": "真正的图像是在光线实际相交点( 相交点) 的地方形成的。 它可以在屏幕上捕捉, 通常会被对象反转 。",
  "What is a virtual image?": "什么是虚拟图像?",
  "A virtual image is formed at a location where light rays, when extended backward, appear to converge. The light does not actually pass through the image location, so it cannot be projected on a screen.": "虚拟图像是在光线( 延伸后向) 似乎会聚集的位置形成。 光线实际上不会穿过图像位置, 因此无法在屏幕上投射 。",
  "What is the focal point of a lens or mirror?": "什么是镜头或镜子的焦点?",
  "The focal point (F) is the point at which rays parallel to the principal axis converge after reflection (mirror) or refraction (lens), or the point from which they appear to diverge for diverging optics.": "联络点(F)是反射(mirror)或折射( lens)后与主轴平行的射线汇合点,或不同光学的射线似乎偏离的点。",
  "What is magnification in optics?": "光学中的放大作用是什么?",
  "Magnification m = hi/ho = -di/do is the ratio of image size to object size. |m| > 1 means enlarged, |m| < 1 means reduced. The sign indicates orientation (positive = upright, negative = inverted).": "放大 m = hi/ ho = - di/ do 是图像大小与对象大小之比 。\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\可以\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",
  "What is the lensmaker's equation?": "透镜器的方程式是什么?",
  "The lensmaker's equation: 1/f = (n-1)(1/R1 - 1/R2) relates the focal length to the lens material's index of refraction (n) and the radii of curvature of its two surfaces (R1, R2).": "透镜器的方程: 1/f = (n-1)(1/R1 - 1/R2) 与透镜材料的折射指数(n) 和其两个表面的曲度(R1, R2) 相挂钩的焦距。",
  "What is the principal axis of a mirror or lens?": "镜像或镜头的主轴是什么?",
  "The principal axis is the imaginary line that passes through the center of the optical element and is perpendicular to its surface. The focal point and center of curvature lie on this axis.": "主轴是穿过光学元素中心并直通其表面的假想线。此轴的焦点和曲线中心位于此轴上。",
  "What is spherical aberration?": "什么是球体畸变?",
  "Spherical aberration occurs because spherical mirrors and lenses focus rays at different distances from the center at slightly different points. It causes blurring and can be corrected with parabolic mirrors or aspheric lenses.": "球体畸变发生是因为球面镜和镜片与中心距离不同的地方的焦点射线相距略微不同点。它造成模糊,可以用抛光镜或球面镜进行校正。",
  "What is chromatic aberration?": "什么是色差?",
  "Chromatic aberration occurs because the index of refraction varies with wavelength (dispersion). Different colors focus at different distances, creating color fringes around images. It is corrected using achromatic doublets.": "出现色差是因为折射指数随波长( 分散度) 不同而变化。 不同距离的颜色焦点不同, 在图像周围产生颜色边缘。 使用色谱双曲来校正它 。",
  "A converging lens with f = 20 cm forms an image of an object placed 15 cm from the lens. What is the magnification?": "F = 20 cm 的相融合镜头形成一个从镜头中放置 15 cm 的物体的图像。放大值是什么?",
  "1/20 = 1/15 + 1/di. 1/di = 1/20 - 1/15 = 3/60 - 4/60 = -1/60. di = -60 cm (virtual). m = -di/do = -(-60)/15 = +4 (virtual, upright, enlarged).": "1/20 = 1/15 + 1/di. 1/di = 1/20 - 1/15 = 3/60 - 4/60 = - 1/60. di = - 60厘米(虚拟)。 m = - di/do = - (-60) 15 = +4(虚拟、正直、扩大)。",
  "A dentist uses a concave mirror with a focal length of 3 cm. The mirror is held 2 cm from a patient's tooth. What is the magnification of the image?": "牙科医生使用3厘米的焦距为3厘米的凝固镜。 镜像从病人的牙齿上扣住2厘米。 图像的放大作用是什么?",
  "1/3 = 1/2 + 1/di. 1/di = 1/3 - 1/2 = 2/6 - 3/6 = -1/6. di = -6 cm (virtual). m = -(-6)/2 = +3 (upright and magnified, which is what the dentist needs).": "1/3 = 1/2 + 1/di. 1/di = 1/3 - 1/2 = 2/6 - 3/6 = - 1/6. di = - 6厘米(虚拟)。 m = - (6)/2 = + 3(直立和放大,这是牙医需要的)。",
  "An optometrist prescribes a lens with power -2.5 diopters. What is the focal length and type of this lens?": "Opopometrist 开出一个带电源 - 2.5 diopters 的镜片。 这个镜片的焦距和类型是什么 ?",
  "f = 1/P = 1/(-2.5) = -0.4 m = -40 cm. The negative focal length indicates a diverging (concave) lens, used to correct myopia (nearsightedness).": "f = 1/P = 1/(-2.5) = -0.4米 = -40厘米。负焦距表示一个不同的(凝固)透镜,用于纠正近视(近视)。",
  "A convex security mirror in a store has a focal length of -60 cm. A shoplifter stands 3 m away. Where does the image appear and what is the magnification?": "商店的雕塑安全镜的焦距为 -60厘米。 商店行窃者站在3米外。 图像在哪里出现, 放大效果是什么 ?",
  "1/f = 1/do + 1/di: 1/(-60) = 1/300 + 1/di. 1/di = -1/60 - 1/300 = -5/300 - 1/300 = -6/300 = -1/50. di = -50 cm. m = -(-50)/300 = +0.167 (virtual, upright, reduced).": "1/f = 1/f = 1/do + 1/di: 1/(60) = 1/300 + 1/di. 1/di = -1/60 - 1/300 = - 5/300 - 1/300 = - 6/300 = - 1/50。 di = - 50厘米 m = - (-50)/300 = + 0.167 (虚拟、直立、缩小)。",
  "A telescope objective lens has f = 100 cm and the eyepiece has f = 5 cm. What is the angular magnification of the telescope?": "望远镜的瞄准镜有f = 100厘米,眼镜有f = 5厘米。望远镜的角放大度是多少?",
  "Angular magnification of a telescope: M = -f_objective/f_eyepiece = -100/5 = -20. The magnitude is 20x (the negative sign indicates an inverted image).": "望远镜的角放大度: M = -f_ 目标/f_ 瞄准镜 = - 100/5 = - 20。星度为 20x(负符号表示反向图像)。",
  "Two thin lenses with focal lengths f1 = 20 cm and f2 = -30 cm are placed in contact. What is the effective focal length of the combination?": "两个有焦距f1 = 20 cm 和 f2 = - 30 cm 的薄镜被放置在接触处。组合的有效焦距是多少?",
  "For thin lenses in contact: 1/f = 1/f1 + 1/f2 = 1/20 + 1/(-30) = 3/60 - 2/60 = 1/60. So f = 60 cm.": "接触的薄镜头: 1/f = 1/f1 + 1/f2 = 1/20 + 1/(30) = 3/60-2/60 = 1/60。",
  "A compound microscope has an objective lens (f = 0.5 cm) and an eyepiece (f = 2.5 cm). The tube length is 16 cm. What is the total magnification when the final image is at the near point (25 cm)?": "复合显微镜有客观透镜(f=0.5厘米)和眼镜(f=2.5厘米),管长为16厘米。当最后图像接近(25厘米)时,总放大度是多少?",
  "M_total = -(L/f_obj)(25/f_eye) = -(16/0.5)(25/2.5) = -32 * 10 = -320x.": "M_总计 = -(L/f_obj)(25/f_eye) = -(16/0.5)(25/2.5) = - 32 * 10 = - 320x。",
  "A photographer uses a camera with a 50 mm lens to photograph a person 5 m away. What is the image distance (distance from lens to film/sensor)?": "摄影师用50毫米镜头照相机拍摄距离5米远的人的照片。 图像距离(从镜头到电影/传感器的距离)是多少?",
  "1/50 = 1/5000 + 1/di (all in mm). 1/di = 1/50 - 1/5000 = 100/5000 - 1/5000 = 99/5000. di = 5000/99 = 50.5 mm. The image forms very close to the focal length.": "1/50 = 1/5000 + 1/di(全毫米)。 1/di = 1/50 - 1/5000 = 100/5000 - 1/5000 = 99/5000。di = 5000/99 = 50.5毫米。图像与焦距非常接近。",
  "A virtual image is one that:": "虚拟图像是:",
  "A virtual image is formed where light rays appear to diverge from but do not actually pass through. It cannot be captured on a screen but can be seen by looking through the optical device.": "当光线似乎与光线不同但实际上没有通过时,就形成了虚拟图像。光线无法在屏幕上捕捉,但可以通过光学设备看到。",
  "When an object is placed between the focal point and a concave mirror, the image is:": "当一个对象被放置在焦点和凝聚镜面之间时,图像是:",
  "When an object is between the focal point and a concave mirror, the reflected rays diverge and appear to come from behind the mirror, creating a virtual, upright, and magnified image.": "当一个物体在焦点和混凝土镜子之间时,反射的射线不同,似乎来自镜子后面,形成虚拟的、直立的和放大的图像。",
  "A convex mirror always produces images that are:": "浮雕镜面总是产生如下图像:",
  "A convex (diverging) mirror always produces virtual, upright, and reduced images, regardless of object distance. This is why convex mirrors are used as wide-angle security mirrors.": "相形镜( 相形反射) 总是生成虚拟的、 直立的和缩小的图像, 不论对象距离 。 因此, 相形镜( 相形反射) 被使用为宽角的安全镜 。",
  "When an object is placed at twice the focal length from a converging lens, the image is:": "当一个对象被放置在离集合镜头的焦距两倍处时,图像是:",
  "When do = 2f, by the lens equation: 1/f = 1/(2f) + 1/di, giving di = 2f. The image is real, inverted, and the same size as the object (m = -1).": "当 = 2f 时, 透镜方程 : 1/f = 1/(2f) + 1/ di, 给 di = 2f 。 图像是真实的, 反转的, 大小与对象( m = - 1) 相同 。",
  "An object is placed 30 cm from a concave mirror with focal length 10 cm. Where is the image formed?": "对象从焦距10厘米的凝聚镜中放置30厘米。 图像在哪里形成?",
  "Using 1/f = 1/do + 1/di: 1/10 = 1/30 + 1/di. 1/di = 1/10 - 1/30 = 3/30 - 1/30 = 2/30. di = 15 cm (in front of the mirror, real image).": "使用 1/f = 1/do + 1/di: 1/10 = 1/30 + 1/di. 1/di = 1/10 - 1/30 = 3/30 - 1/30 = 2/30. di = 15厘米(镜子前,真实图像)。"
}